{
  "book": "1nephi",
  "bookName": "1 Nephi",
  "chapter": 16,
  "voice": {
    "provider": "elevenlabs",
    "voice_id": "ddDFRErfhdc2asyySOG5",
    "model_id": "eleven_multilingual_v2",
    "settings": {
      "stability": 0.5,
      "similarity_boost": 0.75,
      "style": 0.35,
      "use_speaker_boost": true
    },
    "name": "Samuel"
  },
  "pauses": {
    "line_ms": 180,
    "verse_ms": 500
  },
  "duration": 542.954,
  "lines": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 2.601,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And now after I, Nephi, had made an end",
      "verse": "16:1",
      "lineIndex": 1
    },
    {
      "start": 2.781,
      "end": 5.846,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "of speaking to my brothers, behold they said to me:",
      "verse": "16:1",
      "lineIndex": 2
    },
    {
      "start": 6.026,
      "end": 8.069,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "You have declared to us hard things,",
      "verse": "16:1",
      "lineIndex": 3
    },
    {
      "start": 8.249,
      "end": 10.385,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "more than we are able to bear.",
      "verse": "16:1",
      "lineIndex": 4
    },
    {
      "start": 11.065,
      "end": 12.644,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then I said to them",
      "verse": "16:2",
      "lineIndex": 5
    },
    {
      "start": 12.824,
      "end": 16.679,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "that I knew that I had spoken hard things against the wicked,",
      "verse": "16:2",
      "lineIndex": 6
    },
    {
      "start": 16.859,
      "end": 18.392,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "according to the truth;",
      "verse": "16:2",
      "lineIndex": 7
    },
    {
      "start": 18.572,
      "end": 21.08,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and the righteous have I justified,",
      "verse": "16:2",
      "lineIndex": 8
    },
    {
      "start": 21.26,
      "end": 24.929,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and testified that they should be lifted up at the last day;",
      "verse": "16:2",
      "lineIndex": 9
    },
    {
      "start": 25.109,
      "end": 27.756,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "so, the guilty takes the truth to be hard,",
      "verse": "16:2",
      "lineIndex": 10
    },
    {
      "start": 27.936,
      "end": 30.49,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "for it cuts them to the very center.",
      "verse": "16:2",
      "lineIndex": 11
    },
    {
      "start": 31.17,
      "end": 33.956,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And now my brothers, if you were righteous",
      "verse": "16:3",
      "lineIndex": 12
    },
    {
      "start": 34.136,
      "end": 36.783,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and were willing to listen to the truth,",
      "verse": "16:3",
      "lineIndex": 13
    },
    {
      "start": 36.963,
      "end": 38.588,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and give heed to it,",
      "verse": "16:3",
      "lineIndex": 14
    },
    {
      "start": 38.768,
      "end": 41.462,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "that you might walk uprightly before God,",
      "verse": "16:3",
      "lineIndex": 15
    },
    {
      "start": 41.642,
      "end": 43.128,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "then you would not complain",
      "verse": "16:3",
      "lineIndex": 16
    },
    {
      "start": 43.308,
      "end": 45.026,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "because of the truth, and say:",
      "verse": "16:3",
      "lineIndex": 17
    },
    {
      "start": 45.206,
      "end": 47.389,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "You speakest hard things against us.",
      "verse": "16:3",
      "lineIndex": 18
    },
    {
      "start": 48.069,
      "end": 51.831,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then I, Nephi, urged my brothers, with all diligence,",
      "verse": "16:4",
      "lineIndex": 20
    },
    {
      "start": 52.011,
      "end": 54.194,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "to keep the commandments of the Lord.",
      "verse": "16:4",
      "lineIndex": 21
    },
    {
      "start": 54.874,
      "end": 57.753,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then they humbled themselves before the Lord;",
      "verse": "16:5",
      "lineIndex": 22
    },
    {
      "start": 57.933,
      "end": 61.044,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "so much so that I had joy and great hopes of them,",
      "verse": "16:5",
      "lineIndex": 23
    },
    {
      "start": 61.224,
      "end": 64.196,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "that they would walk in the paths of righteousness.",
      "verse": "16:5",
      "lineIndex": 24
    },
    {
      "start": 64.876,
      "end": 69.102,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "Now, all these things were said and done as my father dwelt in a tent",
      "verse": "16:6",
      "lineIndex": 26
    },
    {
      "start": 69.282,
      "end": 71.697,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "in the valley which he called Lemuel.",
      "verse": "16:6",
      "lineIndex": 27
    },
    {
      "start": 72.377,
      "end": 74.002,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then I, Nephi,",
      "verse": "16:7",
      "lineIndex": 28
    },
    {
      "start": 74.182,
      "end": 77.061,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "took one of the daughters of Ishmael to wife;",
      "verse": "16:7",
      "lineIndex": 29
    },
    {
      "start": 77.241,
      "end": 81.049,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and also, my brothers took of the daughters of Ishmael to wife;",
      "verse": "16:7",
      "lineIndex": 30
    },
    {
      "start": 81.229,
      "end": 85.084,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and also Zoram took the eldest daughter of Ishmael to wife.",
      "verse": "16:7",
      "lineIndex": 31
    },
    {
      "start": 85.764,
      "end": 87.947,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And thus my father had fulfilled",
      "verse": "16:8",
      "lineIndex": 32
    },
    {
      "start": 88.127,
      "end": 91.146,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "all the commandments of the Lord which had been given to him.",
      "verse": "16:8",
      "lineIndex": 33
    },
    {
      "start": 91.326,
      "end": 94.716,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And also, I, Nephi, had been blessed of the Lord greatly.",
      "verse": "16:8",
      "lineIndex": 34
    },
    {
      "start": 95.396,
      "end": 98.647,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then the voice of the Lord spoke to my father by night,",
      "verse": "16:9",
      "lineIndex": 36
    },
    {
      "start": 98.827,
      "end": 101.242,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and commanded him that on the morrow",
      "verse": "16:9",
      "lineIndex": 37
    },
    {
      "start": 101.422,
      "end": 104.719,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "he should take his journey into the wilderness.",
      "verse": "16:9",
      "lineIndex": 38
    },
    {
      "start": 105.399,
      "end": 107.953,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then as my father arose in the morning,",
      "verse": "16:10",
      "lineIndex": 40
    },
    {
      "start": 108.133,
      "end": 110.362,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and went forth to the tent door,",
      "verse": "16:10",
      "lineIndex": 41
    },
    {
      "start": 110.542,
      "end": 112.353,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "to his great astonishment",
      "verse": "16:10",
      "lineIndex": 42
    },
    {
      "start": 112.533,
      "end": 116.48,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "he saw upon the ground a round ball of curious workmanship;",
      "verse": "16:10",
      "lineIndex": 43
    },
    {
      "start": 116.66,
      "end": 118.471,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and it was of fine brass.",
      "verse": "16:10",
      "lineIndex": 44
    },
    {
      "start": 118.651,
      "end": 120.787,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And within the ball were two spindles;",
      "verse": "16:10",
      "lineIndex": 45
    },
    {
      "start": 120.967,
      "end": 122.917,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and the one pointed the way",
      "verse": "16:10",
      "lineIndex": 46
    },
    {
      "start": 123.097,
      "end": 125.605,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "where we should go into the wilderness.",
      "verse": "16:10",
      "lineIndex": 47
    },
    {
      "start": 126.285,
      "end": 128.143,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then we gathered together",
      "verse": "16:11",
      "lineIndex": 48
    },
    {
      "start": 128.323,
      "end": 131.713,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "whatsoever things we should carry into the wilderness,",
      "verse": "16:11",
      "lineIndex": 49
    },
    {
      "start": 131.893,
      "end": 135.748,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and all the remainder of our provisions which the Lord had given to us;",
      "verse": "16:11",
      "lineIndex": 50
    },
    {
      "start": 135.928,
      "end": 138.25,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and we took seed of every kind",
      "verse": "16:11",
      "lineIndex": 51
    },
    {
      "start": 138.43,
      "end": 140.891,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "that we might carry into the wilderness.",
      "verse": "16:11",
      "lineIndex": 52
    },
    {
      "start": 141.571,
      "end": 143.243,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then we took our tents",
      "verse": "16:12",
      "lineIndex": 53
    },
    {
      "start": 143.423,
      "end": 146.767,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and depart into the wilderness, across the river Laman.",
      "verse": "16:12",
      "lineIndex": 54
    },
    {
      "start": 147.447,
      "end": 150.419,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then we traveled for the space of four days,",
      "verse": "16:13",
      "lineIndex": 56
    },
    {
      "start": 150.599,
      "end": 153.2,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "nearly a south-southeast direction,",
      "verse": "16:13",
      "lineIndex": 57
    },
    {
      "start": 153.38,
      "end": 155.423,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and we pitched our tents again;",
      "verse": "16:13",
      "lineIndex": 58
    },
    {
      "start": 155.603,
      "end": 158.482,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and we called the name of the place Shazer.",
      "verse": "16:13",
      "lineIndex": 59
    },
    {
      "start": 159.162,
      "end": 161.67,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then we took our bows and our arrows,",
      "verse": "16:14",
      "lineIndex": 61
    },
    {
      "start": 161.85,
      "end": 165.658,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and go forth into the wilderness to kill food for our families;",
      "verse": "16:14",
      "lineIndex": 62
    },
    {
      "start": 165.838,
      "end": 168.949,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and after we had killed food for our families",
      "verse": "16:14",
      "lineIndex": 63
    },
    {
      "start": 169.129,
      "end": 171.73,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "we returned again to our families",
      "verse": "16:14",
      "lineIndex": 64
    },
    {
      "start": 171.91,
      "end": 174.464,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "in the wilderness, to the place of Shazer.",
      "verse": "16:14",
      "lineIndex": 65
    },
    {
      "start": 174.644,
      "end": 177.477,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And we went forth again in the wilderness,",
      "verse": "16:14",
      "lineIndex": 66
    },
    {
      "start": 177.657,
      "end": 179.561,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "following the same direction,",
      "verse": "16:14",
      "lineIndex": 67
    },
    {
      "start": 179.741,
      "end": 183.224,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "keeping in the most fertile parts of the wilderness,",
      "verse": "16:14",
      "lineIndex": 68
    },
    {
      "start": 183.404,
      "end": 186.098,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "which were in the borders near the Red Sea.",
      "verse": "16:14",
      "lineIndex": 69
    },
    {
      "start": 186.778,
      "end": 189.657,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then we traveled for the space of many days,",
      "verse": "16:15",
      "lineIndex": 70
    },
    {
      "start": 189.837,
      "end": 191.416,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "slaying food by the way,",
      "verse": "16:15",
      "lineIndex": 71
    },
    {
      "start": 191.596,
      "end": 194.011,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "with our bows and our arrows",
      "verse": "16:15",
      "lineIndex": 72
    },
    {
      "start": 194.191,
      "end": 196.374,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and our stones and our slings.",
      "verse": "16:15",
      "lineIndex": 73
    },
    {
      "start": 197.054,
      "end": 199.701,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And we followed the directions of the ball,",
      "verse": "16:16",
      "lineIndex": 74
    },
    {
      "start": 199.881,
      "end": 203.132,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "which led us in the more fertile parts of the wilderness.",
      "verse": "16:16",
      "lineIndex": 75
    },
    {
      "start": 203.812,
      "end": 207.109,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And after we had traveled for the space of many days,",
      "verse": "16:17",
      "lineIndex": 76
    },
    {
      "start": 207.289,
      "end": 210.308,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "we pitched our tents for the space of a time,",
      "verse": "16:17",
      "lineIndex": 77
    },
    {
      "start": 210.488,
      "end": 213.089,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "that we might again rest ourselves",
      "verse": "16:17",
      "lineIndex": 78
    },
    {
      "start": 213.269,
      "end": 216.009,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and obtain food for our families.",
      "verse": "16:17",
      "lineIndex": 79
    },
    {
      "start": 216.689,
      "end": 219.893,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then as I, Nephi, went forth to kill food,",
      "verse": "16:18",
      "lineIndex": 81
    },
    {
      "start": 220.073,
      "end": 221.745,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "behold, I broke my bow,",
      "verse": "16:18",
      "lineIndex": 82
    },
    {
      "start": 221.925,
      "end": 224.061,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "which was made of fine steel;",
      "verse": "16:18",
      "lineIndex": 83
    },
    {
      "start": 224.241,
      "end": 225.959,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and after I broke my bow,",
      "verse": "16:18",
      "lineIndex": 84
    },
    {
      "start": 226.139,
      "end": 228.275,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "behold, my brothers were angry with me",
      "verse": "16:18",
      "lineIndex": 85
    },
    {
      "start": 228.455,
      "end": 230.545,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "because of the loss of my bow,",
      "verse": "16:18",
      "lineIndex": 86
    },
    {
      "start": 230.725,
      "end": 232.443,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "for we obtained no food.",
      "verse": "16:18",
      "lineIndex": 87
    },
    {
      "start": 233.123,
      "end": 236.234,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then we returned without food to our families,",
      "verse": "16:19",
      "lineIndex": 88
    },
    {
      "start": 236.414,
      "end": 239.618,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and being much fatigued, because of their journeying,",
      "verse": "16:19",
      "lineIndex": 89
    },
    {
      "start": 239.798,
      "end": 242.12,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "they suffered much for the want of food.",
      "verse": "16:19",
      "lineIndex": 90
    },
    {
      "start": 242.8,
      "end": 246.283,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then Laman and Lemuel and the sons of Ishmael",
      "verse": "16:20",
      "lineIndex": 91
    },
    {
      "start": 246.463,
      "end": 248.228,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "began to murmur greatly,",
      "verse": "16:20",
      "lineIndex": 92
    },
    {
      "start": 248.408,
      "end": 252.077,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "because of their sufferings and hardships in the wilderness;",
      "verse": "16:20",
      "lineIndex": 93
    },
    {
      "start": 252.257,
      "end": 256.019,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and also my father began to complain against the Lord his God;",
      "verse": "16:20",
      "lineIndex": 94
    },
    {
      "start": 256.199,
      "end": 258.66,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "yes, and they were all very sorrowful,",
      "verse": "16:20",
      "lineIndex": 95
    },
    {
      "start": 258.84,
      "end": 261.301,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "even that they complained against the Lord.",
      "verse": "16:20",
      "lineIndex": 96
    },
    {
      "start": 261.981,
      "end": 263.374,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "Now I, Nephi,",
      "verse": "16:21",
      "lineIndex": 97
    },
    {
      "start": 263.554,
      "end": 268.105,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "having been afflicted with my brothers because of the loss of my bow,",
      "verse": "16:21",
      "lineIndex": 98
    },
    {
      "start": 268.285,
      "end": 270.607,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and their bows having lost their springs,",
      "verse": "16:21",
      "lineIndex": 99
    },
    {
      "start": 270.787,
      "end": 272.923,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "it began to be very difficult,",
      "verse": "16:21",
      "lineIndex": 100
    },
    {
      "start": 273.103,
      "end": 276.122,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "yes, so much so that we could obtain no food.",
      "verse": "16:21",
      "lineIndex": 101
    },
    {
      "start": 276.802,
      "end": 279.728,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then I, Nephi, spoke much to my brothers,",
      "verse": "16:22",
      "lineIndex": 102
    },
    {
      "start": 279.908,
      "end": 282.602,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "because they had hardened their hearts again,",
      "verse": "16:22",
      "lineIndex": 103
    },
    {
      "start": 282.782,
      "end": 285.336,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "even to complaining against the Lord their God.",
      "verse": "16:22",
      "lineIndex": 104
    },
    {
      "start": 286.016,
      "end": 288.756,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then I, Nephi, made out of wood a bow,",
      "verse": "16:23",
      "lineIndex": 106
    },
    {
      "start": 288.936,
      "end": 291.49,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and out of a straight stick, an arrow;",
      "verse": "16:23",
      "lineIndex": 107
    },
    {
      "start": 291.67,
      "end": 294.828,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "so, I armed myself with a bow and an arrow,",
      "verse": "16:23",
      "lineIndex": 108
    },
    {
      "start": 295.008,
      "end": 297.144,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "with a sling and with stones.",
      "verse": "16:23",
      "lineIndex": 109
    },
    {
      "start": 297.324,
      "end": 298.949,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And I said to my father:",
      "verse": "16:23",
      "lineIndex": 110
    },
    {
      "start": 299.129,
      "end": 301.312,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "Where shall I go to obtain food?",
      "verse": "16:23",
      "lineIndex": 111
    },
    {
      "start": 301.992,
      "end": 304.035,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then he inquired of the Lord,",
      "verse": "16:24",
      "lineIndex": 112
    },
    {
      "start": 304.215,
      "end": 307.28,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "for they had humbled themselves because of my words;",
      "verse": "16:24",
      "lineIndex": 113
    },
    {
      "start": 307.46,
      "end": 310.989,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "for I said many things to them in the energy of my soul.",
      "verse": "16:24",
      "lineIndex": 114
    },
    {
      "start": 311.669,
      "end": 314.641,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then the voice of the Lord came to my father;",
      "verse": "16:25",
      "lineIndex": 115
    },
    {
      "start": 314.821,
      "end": 316.539,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and he was truly chastened",
      "verse": "16:25",
      "lineIndex": 116
    },
    {
      "start": 316.719,
      "end": 319.087,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "because of his murmuring against the Lord,",
      "verse": "16:25",
      "lineIndex": 117
    },
    {
      "start": 319.267,
      "end": 323.4,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "so much so that he was brought down into the depths of sorrow.",
      "verse": "16:25",
      "lineIndex": 118
    },
    {
      "start": 324.08,
      "end": 326.356,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then the voice of the Lord said to him:",
      "verse": "16:26",
      "lineIndex": 119
    },
    {
      "start": 326.536,
      "end": 327.929,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "Look upon the ball,",
      "verse": "16:26",
      "lineIndex": 120
    },
    {
      "start": 328.109,
      "end": 330.431,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and behold the things which are written.",
      "verse": "16:26",
      "lineIndex": 121
    },
    {
      "start": 331.111,
      "end": 333.572,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then when my father saw the things",
      "verse": "16:27",
      "lineIndex": 122
    },
    {
      "start": 333.752,
      "end": 336.167,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "which were written upon the ball,",
      "verse": "16:27",
      "lineIndex": 123
    },
    {
      "start": 336.347,
      "end": 338.623,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "he feared and tremble greatly,",
      "verse": "16:27",
      "lineIndex": 124
    },
    {
      "start": 338.803,
      "end": 342.518,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and also my brothers and the sons of Ishmael and our wives.",
      "verse": "16:27",
      "lineIndex": 125
    },
    {
      "start": 343.198,
      "end": 346.681,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then I, Nephi, saw the pointers which were in the ball,",
      "verse": "16:28",
      "lineIndex": 127
    },
    {
      "start": 346.861,
      "end": 348.068,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "they worked",
      "verse": "16:28",
      "lineIndex": 128
    },
    {
      "start": 348.248,
      "end": 353.774,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "according to the faith and diligence and heed which we gave to them.",
      "verse": "16:28",
      "lineIndex": 129
    },
    {
      "start": 354.454,
      "end": 358.03,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And there was also written upon them a new writing,",
      "verse": "16:29",
      "lineIndex": 130
    },
    {
      "start": 358.21,
      "end": 360.021,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "which was plain to be read,",
      "verse": "16:29",
      "lineIndex": 131
    },
    {
      "start": 360.201,
      "end": 362.384,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "which gave us understanding",
      "verse": "16:29",
      "lineIndex": 132
    },
    {
      "start": 362.564,
      "end": 365.722,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "concerning the ways of the Lord; and it was written",
      "verse": "16:29",
      "lineIndex": 133
    },
    {
      "start": 365.902,
      "end": 368.224,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and changed from time to time,",
      "verse": "16:29",
      "lineIndex": 134
    },
    {
      "start": 368.404,
      "end": 371.887,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "according to the faith and diligence which we gave to it.",
      "verse": "16:29",
      "lineIndex": 135
    },
    {
      "start": 372.067,
      "end": 377.083,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And thus we see that by small means the Lord can bring about great things.",
      "verse": "16:29",
      "lineIndex": 136
    },
    {
      "start": 377.763,
      "end": 381.664,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then I, Nephi, went forth up into the top of the mountain,",
      "verse": "16:30",
      "lineIndex": 138
    },
    {
      "start": 381.844,
      "end": 384.909,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "according to the directions which were given upon the ball.",
      "verse": "16:30",
      "lineIndex": 139
    },
    {
      "start": 385.589,
      "end": 387.539,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then I killed wild beasts,",
      "verse": "16:31",
      "lineIndex": 140
    },
    {
      "start": 387.719,
      "end": 391.295,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "so much so that I obtained food for our families.",
      "verse": "16:31",
      "lineIndex": 141
    },
    {
      "start": 391.975,
      "end": 394.343,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then I returned to our tents,",
      "verse": "16:32",
      "lineIndex": 142
    },
    {
      "start": 394.523,
      "end": 397.031,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "bearing the beasts which I had killed;",
      "verse": "16:32",
      "lineIndex": 143
    },
    {
      "start": 397.211,
      "end": 400.09,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and now when they saw that I had obtained food,",
      "verse": "16:32",
      "lineIndex": 144
    },
    {
      "start": 400.27,
      "end": 402.081,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "how great was their joy!",
      "verse": "16:32",
      "lineIndex": 145
    },
    {
      "start": 402.261,
      "end": 405.047,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then they humbled themselves before the Lord,",
      "verse": "16:32",
      "lineIndex": 146
    },
    {
      "start": 405.227,
      "end": 406.713,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and gave thanks to him.",
      "verse": "16:32",
      "lineIndex": 147
    },
    {
      "start": 407.393,
      "end": 409.994,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then we did again take our journey,",
      "verse": "16:33",
      "lineIndex": 148
    },
    {
      "start": 410.174,
      "end": 413.564,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "traveling nearly the same course as in the beginning;",
      "verse": "16:33",
      "lineIndex": 149
    },
    {
      "start": 413.744,
      "end": 415.787,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and after we had traveled",
      "verse": "16:33",
      "lineIndex": 150
    },
    {
      "start": 415.967,
      "end": 419.218,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "for the space of many days we pitched our tents again,",
      "verse": "16:33",
      "lineIndex": 151
    },
    {
      "start": 419.398,
      "end": 422.045,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "that we might stay for the space of a time.",
      "verse": "16:33",
      "lineIndex": 152
    },
    {
      "start": 422.725,
      "end": 424.35,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then Ishmael died,",
      "verse": "16:34",
      "lineIndex": 154
    },
    {
      "start": 424.53,
      "end": 427.549,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and was buried in the place which was called Nahom.",
      "verse": "16:34",
      "lineIndex": 155
    },
    {
      "start": 428.229,
      "end": 431.619,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then the daughters of Ishmael did mourn greatly,",
      "verse": "16:35",
      "lineIndex": 156
    },
    {
      "start": 431.799,
      "end": 433.796,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "because of the loss of their father,",
      "verse": "16:35",
      "lineIndex": 157
    },
    {
      "start": 433.976,
      "end": 437.041,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and because of their hardships in the wilderness;",
      "verse": "16:35",
      "lineIndex": 158
    },
    {
      "start": 437.221,
      "end": 439.636,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and they complained against my father,",
      "verse": "16:35",
      "lineIndex": 159
    },
    {
      "start": 439.816,
      "end": 444.367,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "because he had brought them out of the land of Jerusalem, saying:",
      "verse": "16:35",
      "lineIndex": 160
    },
    {
      "start": 444.547,
      "end": 446.126,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "Our father is dead;",
      "verse": "16:35",
      "lineIndex": 161
    },
    {
      "start": 446.306,
      "end": 449.464,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "yes, and we have wandered much in the wilderness,",
      "verse": "16:35",
      "lineIndex": 162
    },
    {
      "start": 449.644,
      "end": 454.845,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and we have suffered much affliction, hunger, thirst, and fatigue;",
      "verse": "16:35",
      "lineIndex": 163
    },
    {
      "start": 455.025,
      "end": 457.161,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and after all these sufferings",
      "verse": "16:35",
      "lineIndex": 164
    },
    {
      "start": 457.341,
      "end": 459.942,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "we must perish in the wilderness with hunger.",
      "verse": "16:35",
      "lineIndex": 165
    },
    {
      "start": 460.622,
      "end": 463.641,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And thus they complained against my father,",
      "verse": "16:36",
      "lineIndex": 166
    },
    {
      "start": 463.821,
      "end": 465.307,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and also against me;",
      "verse": "16:36",
      "lineIndex": 167
    },
    {
      "start": 465.487,
      "end": 468.506,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and they were desirous to return again to Jerusalem.",
      "verse": "16:36",
      "lineIndex": 168
    },
    {
      "start": 469.186,
      "end": 473.041,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And Laman said to Lemuel and also to the sons of Ishmael:",
      "verse": "16:37",
      "lineIndex": 170
    },
    {
      "start": 473.221,
      "end": 475.218,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "Behold, let us kill our father",
      "verse": "16:37",
      "lineIndex": 171
    },
    {
      "start": 475.398,
      "end": 477.488,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and also our brother Nephi,",
      "verse": "16:37",
      "lineIndex": 172
    },
    {
      "start": 477.668,
      "end": 481.383,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "who has taken it upon him to be our ruler and our teacher,",
      "verse": "16:37",
      "lineIndex": 173
    },
    {
      "start": 481.563,
      "end": 483.513,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "who are his elder brothers.",
      "verse": "16:37",
      "lineIndex": 174
    },
    {
      "start": 484.193,
      "end": 486.979,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "Now, he says that the Lord has talked with him,",
      "verse": "16:38",
      "lineIndex": 175
    },
    {
      "start": 487.159,
      "end": 489.899,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and also that angels have ministered to him.",
      "verse": "16:38",
      "lineIndex": 176
    },
    {
      "start": 490.079,
      "end": 492.587,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "But behold, we know that he lies to us;",
      "verse": "16:38",
      "lineIndex": 177
    },
    {
      "start": 492.767,
      "end": 494.485,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and he tells us these things,",
      "verse": "16:38",
      "lineIndex": 178
    },
    {
      "start": 494.665,
      "end": 497.451,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and he works many things by his cunning arts",
      "verse": "16:38",
      "lineIndex": 179
    },
    {
      "start": 497.631,
      "end": 499.628,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "that he may deceive our eyes,",
      "verse": "16:38",
      "lineIndex": 180
    },
    {
      "start": 499.808,
      "end": 501.248,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "thinking, perhaps,",
      "verse": "16:38",
      "lineIndex": 181
    },
    {
      "start": 501.428,
      "end": 505.19,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "that he may lead us away into some strange wilderness;",
      "verse": "16:38",
      "lineIndex": 182
    },
    {
      "start": 505.37,
      "end": 507.413,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and after he has led us away,",
      "verse": "16:38",
      "lineIndex": 183
    },
    {
      "start": 507.593,
      "end": 511.215,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "he has thought to make himself a king and a ruler over us,",
      "verse": "16:38",
      "lineIndex": 184
    },
    {
      "start": 511.395,
      "end": 514.553,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "that he may do with us according to his will and pleasure.",
      "verse": "16:38",
      "lineIndex": 185
    },
    {
      "start": 514.733,
      "end": 516.312,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And after this manner",
      "verse": "16:38",
      "lineIndex": 186
    },
    {
      "start": 516.492,
      "end": 519.836,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "did my brother Laman stir up their hearts to anger.",
      "verse": "16:38",
      "lineIndex": 187
    },
    {
      "start": 520.516,
      "end": 522.42,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then the Lord was with us,",
      "verse": "16:39",
      "lineIndex": 188
    },
    {
      "start": 522.6,
      "end": 525.386,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "indeed, even the voice of the Lord came",
      "verse": "16:39",
      "lineIndex": 189
    },
    {
      "start": 525.566,
      "end": 527.795,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and spoke many words to them,",
      "verse": "16:39",
      "lineIndex": 190
    },
    {
      "start": 527.975,
      "end": 529.647,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and chastened them very;",
      "verse": "16:39",
      "lineIndex": 191
    },
    {
      "start": 529.827,
      "end": 532.799,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and after they were chastened by the voice of the Lord",
      "verse": "16:39",
      "lineIndex": 192
    },
    {
      "start": 532.979,
      "end": 535.162,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "they turned away their anger,",
      "verse": "16:39",
      "lineIndex": 193
    },
    {
      "start": 535.342,
      "end": 537.292,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and repented of their sins,",
      "verse": "16:39",
      "lineIndex": 194
    },
    {
      "start": 537.472,
      "end": 540.583,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "so much so that the Lord blessed us again with food,",
      "verse": "16:39",
      "lineIndex": 195
    },
    {
      "start": 540.763,
      "end": 542.296,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "that we did not perish.",
      "verse": "16:39",
      "lineIndex": 196
    }
  ]
}